Syllabus for SBI Specialist Deputy Manager (Law). 

1) Banking Regulation & Compliance and Legal Aspects

a) RBI’s Constitution and Objectives
b) Banking Regulation Act, 1949
c) Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934
d) Credit Information Bureau (India)
e) Banker-Customer Relationship
f) Payment and Collection of Cheques and Other Negotiable Instruments
g) Types of Collaterals and their Characteristics
h) Foreign Exchange Management Act,1999
i) The Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002

2) Banking Regulated Important Laws

a) Limitation Act, 1993
b) Banker’s Books Evidence Act, 1891
c) The Recovery of Debts due to Banks and Financial Institutions (DRT) Act,1993
d) Securitisation and Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest (SARFAESI) Act, 2002
e) Miscellaneous Provisions Consumer Protection Act, 1986
f) The Banking Ombudsman Scheme, 2006
g) Procedure for Redressal of Grievance
h) Lok Adalats

3) Commercial Laws with Reference to Banking Operation

a) Contracts of Guarantee
b) Contracts of Bailment
c) Contracts of Pledge
d) Contracts of Agency
e) Meaning and Essentials of a Contract of Sale
f) Definition, Meaning and Nature of Partnership
g) Dissolution of a Firm
h) Effects of Non-Registration
i) Definition and Features of Company
j) Types of Companies
k) Memorandum of Association and Articles of Association
l) Doctrines of Ultra/Constructive Notice/Indoor Management
m) Transfer of Property Act, 1882
n) The Right to Information Act, 2005
o) Right to Information and Obligation of Public Authorities
p) Information Technology Act, 2000
